title: The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom Review
author: @paulcantshutup
comment:
Just got a new Switch, and reinstalled Tears of the Kingdom almost immediately. The sensation of coming back to this big open world is so thrilling, and the prospect of adventure so addictive. It's a big, open world out there... and UP there... and DOWN there... and there's just so much to do. This captures a sense of adventurous fun, of lighthearted play, that not much else has been able to in recent years. 

This is the greatest adventure of all time, honestly.

title: The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom Review
author: @せがせがお
comment:
「任天堂バイアス」

と、考えるのは私がひねくれているからでしょうか？

もし、ティアーズ オブ ザ キングダムと全く同じ内容の物を、新規IPとして名も無き開発会社が、「先に」出していたとして、

ホライゾンフォビドゥンウェスト
ツシマ
レッドデットリデンプション2
サイバーパンク2077
スカイリム
アサシンクリードヴァルハラ
ウィッチャー3

などの、タイトルと比較され、本当にティアーズ オブ ザ キングダムがビデオゲーム史上最高だと評価されているのでしょうか？


新規IPなら、

グラフィックがショボすぎる。

閑散としていて、寂しい。

移動が長い。

ゲージ管理がダルい。

戦闘がつまらん。

打撃音がカスカスで手ごたえが無い。

祠が無駄に多いだけで面白味がない。

難しい。

町の楽しさがない。

ストーリーが薄い。

ゲームプレイに高揚感が無く、単調で地味。

フレームレートが低すぎて操作性が悪い。

ただの、ミニゲーム、パズル集だ。

など、もっと表面的な内容の批判で、平均点が下がっているはず。


任天堂、ゼルダ、バイアスで、最初から、プレイヤーの前向きなやる気が違い、

例えば、ウルトラハンドなら、

任天堂、「選択肢が多い」

無名の開発会社、「パズルゲームが遊びたい訳ではない」「めんどくさい」

など、同じ事でも、絶対反応に違いが出るはず。


任天堂以外の新規IPなら全く同じ内容でも、みなさんこんなに素直に遊んでいないだろうし、それどころか、遊んでみることすらしていないのではないでしょうか？

ゼルダでなければ、癖の強い、賛否有って当然のタイトルで、

マニア層に受けるのは理解できるが、この内容で万人向けだとは、ちょっと考えられない。


売れるのは良い事だが、売れているから良い物だという同調圧力だけでなく、もっと「良く出来ているがつまらない」、みたいな、健全な、批評、批判をしながら遊ぶべきだと思います。



以上、失礼いたしました。

お付き合いいただきありがとうございました。

title: The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom Review
author: @nesaaliyah4821
comment: Every IGN review: “this game is a 10/10 if you don’t count all the things that are bad about it!” Totk is 7/10 at the absolute best. The wretched UX/UI design, the interminable grinding which is rewarded only with more grinding, the fact that Link is still underpowered after 100 hours of busy-work side quests, the deeply unmemorable and generic story, the innumerable nonsensical handicaps, the half-baked currency systems—jeez.

title: The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom Review
author: @mrfreeman3904
comment:
*now that I've completed the whole thing*

The way TOTK welcomes creative playstyle is beyond impressive, regardless of whatever permutations/combinations player comes up with its all functional for the most part

Open world traversal in TOTK is such a multi layered action i.e. better than any open world game in existence, it could be its own game

*But the game has so many glaring flaws that wasn't even mentioned here,*

TOTK adds 12 new overworld enemies & 8 new bosses which is very poor in terms of enemy variety & wasn't nearly enough to fill the world properly, the depths probably being the most underwhelming area because there's nothing unique to encounter down there except one Frox enemy. Even the unique dungeon bosses were repeated

Despite the tutorial sky islands being the pinnacle of game design, the rest of the sky islands are essentially samey landmasses & are quite sparse.
Bulk of the sky islands are basically "bring the stone shrines" and gacha zonai machine

The temples dont hold a candle to classic Zelda dungeons despite being somewhat better than the divine beasts, some of them were awful in terms of Zelda standards

This is want sequels were in the past bigger, better and more features, enemies and environments unlike cash grabbing DLCs 4 hours long with few "extra' skins and season passes. title: The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom Review
author: @quentenburnett7296
comment: If Nintendo can do a game of this scale with comparatively few resources (relative to EA, Microsoft, Sony, etc) and have it release without bugs or game breaking performance issues, and without microtransactions or loot boxes, and on hardware that would've been outdated on a console in 2013, then what excuse does the rest of the industry have? The only downside is that it is $70 and that it SHOULD be on more powerful hardware at this point. If Nintendo could just do what Sony and Microsoft do and put their 1st party games on Steam it would be amazing. Imagine Tears running at 4K 120FPS with mod support. You think it has an insane amount of content as is, imagine what could be done with official mods.

To think people are mad at this because
It uses the same Hyrule and re-uses assets
Same game as BotW after waiting 6 years

When there are franchises that are literally the same games with yearly releases

It uses the same Hyrule because IT'S A SEQUEL!  IT'S NOT DLC!
If BotW was a masterpiece, WHY CHANGE IT!?
If you want an OoT game, there will be alternate games if you demand that!


Oh well, I've been spoiling myself on purpose with this game cuz I'm broke and will probably never be able to play it ever and will never be happy ever.
